text.paragraph:
- to avoid excessive sunlight or artificial ultraviolet light while receiving doxycycline and to discontinue therapy if phototoxicity (e.g., skin eruption, etc.) occurs. Sunscreen or sunblock should be considered (See 
                              WARNINGS
                           ).

- to drink fluids liberally along with doxycycline to reduce the risk of esophageal irritation and ulceration (See 
                              ADVERSE REACTIONS
                           ).

- that the absorption of tetracyclines is reduced when taking bismuth subsalicylate (See 
                              Drug Interactions
                           ).
